enhanced_by.reason: The region() method provides the AWS region required for constructing the ARN.
The accountId() method provides the AWS account ID required for constructing the ARN.
The appName() method provides the application name required for constructing the ARN.
The randHex() method provides a random hexadecimal string required for constructing the ARN.
The region() method must be invoked before albARN() to ensure the region is available.
The accountId() method must be invoked before albARN() to ensure the account ID is available.
The appName() method must be invoked before albARN() to ensure the application name is available.
The randHex() method must be invoked before albARN() to ensure the random hexadecimal string is available.
